cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper is about constructing image datasets using textual queries and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for collecting images from the web, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for processing textual queries, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for multi-view and multi-instance learning, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on object detection and image classification, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as the fifth likely sub-category.
